title: Jim Walmsley breaks 50-mile record
content: Jim Walmsley broke the 50-mile record by 13 seconds, finishing in 4 hours, 50 minutes, 7 seconds. Walmsey averaged a 5:48 mile for almost five hours, which is truly remarkable.

title: Project Carbon X and Breaking2
content: Project Carbon X was part promotion and part athletic endeavor, while Breaking2 was a similar stunt and show of athletic display. Project Carbon X was IAAF-approved for world record status while Breaking2 was not. Both are truly remarkable feats.

title: Specialization in athletic performance
content: Both feats seemingly demonstrate a remarkable display of specialization. Generalization and specialization have been on my mind recently as I’m looking forward to reading David Epstein’s new book, Range: Why Generalists Triumph in a Specialized World.
